Difference Between KNN and K-Means
KNN → Supervised learning and used for classification.
K-Means → Unsupervised learning and used for clustering.

Types:
K-Means Clustering → Centroid based
K-Medoids → Representative object based
Agglomerative Clustering → Tree merging based
Divisive Clustering → Tree splitting based
DBSCAN → Density based
Mean Shift → Mean point shifting based
Gaussian Mixture Model → Probability distribution based